The objective of the Absurdity of the Year survey is to consult the rules and regulations that companies and entrepreneurs in the Czech Republic must respect and try to eliminate those that are absurd.
This year, for the fourth time, it is part of the corporate tournament of the publication Hospodá<0xC5><0x99>ské noviny and begins to create hobby also among the general public.
While last year’s edition had the participation of three thousand voters, this year practically reached four thousand.
And it is not surprising, since we still have several legal obligations to spare that must be respected simply to trade.
"Perhaps in terms of the number of papers required for the tax return we are in the first place worldwide," says Karel Havlí<0xC4><0x8D>ek of the Association of Small and Medium-sized Enterprises and Entrepreneurs of the Czech Republic.
For years, the simplification of business rules has been a declared goal of all governments.
