“Economic prosperity cannot be maintained if the state continually puts obstacles on entrepreneurs, so my goal is to eliminate every year a minimum of thirty paragraphs that currently unnecessarily complicate trade,” announced the Minister of Industry and Commerce Martin Kocourek.
Efforts to eliminate absurd regulations do not end in borage.
In 2007, what annoyed people the most was the obligation of the entrepreneur to communicate three days in advance to the business office of the permanent operating area, the intention to go with a stand to a fair or exhibition.
This obligation was eliminated in the new industrial law.
The obligation that ended in second place in number of votes in 2007, i.e. the communication to the office of work by its foreign workers of work trips of up to 30 days, was eliminated in the law of the so-called green card.
The third is the loser.
The Absurdity of 2009 was the regulation for physiotherapists to have in their office a large mirror, a refrigerator and two floor scales.
That is why this year the Ministry of Health issued a communication saying that it had eliminated the obligation to have a refrigerator.
